Description: Fender Japan stratocaster ST54-DMC/VSP vintage Reissue Fender Japan ST54 (1954) Stratocaster vintage reissue. Just in case you are unfamiliar with Fender Japan( made in Japan MIJ or crafted in Japan CIJ ), these guitars are known for the superb craftmanship and quality. In fact, many guitar players, even professionals prefer these guitars over some US made counterparts. Since these Japanese made Fenders are no longer available and also were not allowed in US (new) , in recent years, these guitars are becoming harder to find.Model: Fender Japan ST54-DMC/VSPSerial number: S015245 (2006-2008)Color: SUNBURSTCondition: This is a Fender Japan Stratocaster ST54-DMC/VSP Vintage reissue. This guitar is equipped with 3 Dimarzio Vintage Collection pickups developed by Dimarzio and Fender Japan - only available in Japan. 2 piece ash body, maple neck, 5 way selector switch and Vintage Kluson type tuners . Nitrocellulose lacquer topcoart finish. A nice straight very soft V-shape neck with some minor fret wear - still playable for years. 1 ply white pickguard. The original Dimarzio pickup covers were replaced by the vintage white covers - the original covers will be included. This guitar feels and sounds great. The neck is straight and the action is set low (for a vintage Strat). This guitar has some scratches, but it is in a great condition. It sounds like an old Start but these pickups are known to produce less noise.It weighs 8 Lbs 3oz. (3.7kg)The vintage style pickup covers are installed but the original Dimarzio pickup covers will be included..
